            <fr:title text="Polynomial">Polynomial</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:authors></fr:authors>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>A function <fr:tex display="inline">f: R \to  R</fr:tex> is a <fr:strong>polynomial</fr:strong> with coefficients in ring <fr:tex display="inline">R</fr:tex> if
    there exists  <fr:tex display="inline">n \in  \N </fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline">a_0, a_1, \ldots , a_n \in  R</fr:tex> such that
    <fr:tex display="block">         f(x) = a_0 + a_1 x + a_2 x^2 + \cdots  + a_n x^n     </fr:tex>
    for all <fr:tex display="inline">x \in  R</fr:tex>. We denote the set all polynomials with coefficients in <fr:tex display="inline">R</fr:tex> by <fr:tex display="inline">\mathcal {P}(R)</fr:tex>.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter></fr:backmatter>
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
